<item>
            <title>[SPARK-8010] Implict promote Numeric type to String type in HiveTypeCoercion</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-8010</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;1. Given a query&lt;br/&gt;
`select coalesce(null, 1, &apos;1&apos;) from dual` will cause exception:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  java.lang.RuntimeException: Could not determine return type of Coalesce for IntegerType,StringType&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. Given a query:&lt;br/&gt;
`select case when true then 1 else &apos;1&apos; end from dual` will cause exception:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  java.lang.RuntimeException: Types in CASE WHEN must be the same or coercible to a common type: StringType != IntegerType&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I checked the code, the main cause is the HiveTypeCoercion doesn&apos;t do implicit convert when there is a IntegerType and StringType.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Numeric types can be promoted to string type in case throw exceptions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since Hive will always do this. It need to be fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
